a famous actress...

13:55.223 --> 13:57.524
I'm not gonna tell you
why movie stars are the best.

13:57.526 --> 13:59.158
They just are.

14:00.361 --> 14:02.962
I'm surprised you guys never
talked about this stuff.

14:02.964 --> 14:05.198
Like you and Sheldon have
everything figured out?

14:05.200 --> 14:06.299
Actually,

14:06.301 --> 14:07.267
our relationship agreement

14:07.269 --> 14:09.469
covers a wide array
of scenarios,

14:09.471 --> 14:12.038
including career changes,
financial instability,

14:12.040 --> 14:14.474
intelligent dog uprising...

14:15.175 --> 14:16.943
FYI, we plan on selling out

14:16.945 --> 14:19.112
the human race hard.

14:22.049 --> 14:25.018
In 20 years, who knows
what'll happen with any of us?

14:25.020 --> 14:27.487
I think you and Leonard
will be together.

14:27.489 --> 14:29.055
You do?
Yeah.

14:29.057 --> 14:31.224
I think you're
the best couple I know.

14:31.226 --> 14:32.825
Aw.
That's so sweet.

14:32.827 --> 14:35.228
What the hell?!
Excuse me?

14:35.230 --> 14:36.195
Ah-da-da-da-da!

14:36.197 --> 14:38.164
Let the dead man talk.

14:39.266 --> 14:40.400
So, why do you think that?

14:40.402 --> 14:42.201
Uh, well, I feel like

14:42.203 --> 14:45.271
you guys make each
other better.

14:45.273 --> 14:47.106
Penny brought Leonard
out of his shell.

14:47.108 --> 14:48.341
And it seems like Leonard

14:48.343 --> 14:50.443
makes Penny think more
deeply about the world.

14:50.445 --> 14:51.611
I don't know.

14:51.613 --> 14:54.681
Together, you two kind of
make one awesome person.

14:54.683 --> 14:56.883
Aw, Stuart.

14:56.885 --> 14:59.419
Now I feel bad
for murdering you.

14:59.421 --> 15:02.121
Oh, come on!

15:02.123 --> 15:03.590
Penny did it! I win!

15:03.592 --> 15:06.559
Suck it, jackasses!

15:12.200 --> 15:14.867
Hey, can I come in?

15:14.869 --> 15:16.803
Apparently any man
is welcome in this house.

15:16.805 --> 15:18.938
Why not you?

15:20.741 --> 15:22.375
I thought you were waiting
in the car.

15:22.377 --> 15:24.377
That was an hour ago, Sheldon.

15:24.379 --> 15:26.980
A Jew sits in front of a house
in Texas that long,

15:26.982 --> 15:29.115
"For Sale" signs
start to go up.

15:31.986 --> 15:35.421
I take it things didn't
go smoothly with your mom.

15:35.423 --> 15:37.790
No.

15:37.792 --> 15:40.927
I'm not sure how we're going
to get past this.

15:40.929 --> 15:42.128
You know, I...

15:42.130 --> 15:44.797
I sort of went
through something

15:44.799 --> 15:46.599
like this myself.

15:46.601 --> 15:49.268
Howard, we've all seen
your mother naked.

15:51.572 --> 15:53.973
That woman needs to learn
how to tie a robe.

15:53.975 --> 15:57.543
I'm talking about when
my mom started seeing someone

15:57.545 --> 15:59.846
a couple years
after my dad left.

15:59.848 --> 16:02.682
I didn't know she did.

16:02.684 --> 16:06.252
Yeah, she was dating this guy,

16:06.254 --> 16:10.189
and I was kind of a jerk
to her about it.

16:10.191 --> 16:12.458
What did you do?

16:12.460 --> 16:14.527
Well, let's just say
it was the most vicious

16:14.529 --> 16:17.664
bar mitzvah speech in
the history of Temple Beth El.

16:18.632 --> 16:21.834
Anyway, she broke up with him.

16:21.836 --> 16:23.803
And she's basically

16:23.805 --> 16:26.039
been alone ever since.

16:27.174 --> 16:30.677
She never said it,
but I always felt

16:30.679 --> 16:33.880
I was the reason why.

16:33.882 --> 16:34.847
I'm sorry.

16:34.849 --> 16:36.315
Although,
based on your story,

16:36.317 --> 16:40.253
you absolutely
were the reason why.

16:41.188 --> 16:43.356
All I'm saying is
you might not want

16:43.358 --> 16:46.726
to get in the way
of your mom's happiness.

16:48.328 --> 16:50.563
You may have a point.

16:50.565 --> 16:53.399
I love my mother.

16:53.401 --> 16:57.537
Even if she fornicates
like a demonic weasel.

17:01.508 --> 17:04.510
And the healing begins.

17:08.882 --> 17:09.915
Hello.

17:09.917 --> 17:10.950
Hello.

17:10.952 --> 17:12.285
Are you ready to discuss

17:12.287 --> 17:14.020
this calmly, like adults?

17:14.021 --> 17:16.556
I am.

17:28.836 --> 17:32.038
Shelly, I'm sorry that
you saw what you saw.

17:32.040 --> 17:34.373
I know that this
is hard for you.

17:34.375 --> 17:36.709
I think what most upsets me
about it, Mother,

17:36.711 --> 17:38.478
is the hypocrisy.

17:38.480 --> 17:40.446
Doesn't this contradict

17:40.448 --> 17:43.649
all the religious rules you've
been espousing your whole life?

17:43.651 --> 17:45.151
You're right, it does,
and it's something

17:45.153 --> 17:47.453
that I'm struggling
with these days.

17:47.455 --> 17:49.155
Then why are you doing it?

17:49.157 --> 17:51.991
Because I'm not
perfect, Shelly.

17:51.993 --> 17:54.961
And that man's booty is.

18:00.033 --> 18:03.870
Well, this is confusing for me.

18:03.872 --> 18:06.372
But I don't want to stand
in the way of your happiness.

18:06.374 --> 18:08.341
So...

18:08.343 --> 18:11.010
I'll condemn you internally
while maintaining

18:11.012 --> 18:13.946
an outward appearance
of acceptance.

18:15.048 --> 18:18.518
That is very Christian of you.

18:20.788 --> 18:22.722
Mother, if you're going
to conduct your life

18:22.724 --> 18:25.124
in this fashion,
then I should let you know

18:25.126 --> 18:28.294
that the world has changed
since you were a young woman.

18:28.296 --> 18:29.662
You know,
it's not all sock hops,

18:29.664 --> 18:33.466
soda jerks
and segregation anymore.

18:33.468 --> 18:37.036
How old do you think I am?

18:37.038 --> 18:40.706
My point is that you're going
to need to be careful.

18:40.708 --> 18:42.041
You used to be protected

18:42.043 --> 18:44.811
by your pre-Enlightenment
mythology,

18:44.813 --> 18:47.513
but now you're going
to need a stronger friend

18:47.515 --> 18:50.550
named latex.

18:51.752 --> 18:55.755
Are you having the
sex talk with me?

18:55.757 --> 18:57.089
Well, someone has to.

18:57.091 --> 18:59.625
Oh, dear Lord!
Yeah, well...

18:59.627 --> 19:02.195
No, don't look to Him.
He's mad at you right now.

19:12.162 --> 19:13.763
Oh, come on, don't pout.

19:13.765 --> 19:15.465
I'm sorry I ruined your game.

19:15.467 --> 19:17.633
I'm not pouting, I'm brooding.

19:17.635 --> 19:20.837
Which is how sexy men pout.

19:22.406 --> 19:24.173
It actually was kind of fun.

19:24.175 --> 19:25.274
You're just saying that.

19:25.276 --> 19:27.410
Yeah.

19:30.014 --> 19:31.981
I liked the time travel element.

19:31.983 --> 19:34.183
Thank you.
I thought it was inspired.

19:34.185 --> 19:35.952
It was. By <i>Terminator.</i>

19:37.254 --> 19:38.654
Well, I hope 20 years from now,

19:38.656 --> 19:39.856
we really are all still together

19:39.858 --> 19:40.857
and still friends.

19:40.859 --> 19:42.291
Definitely.
Of course.

19:42.293 --> 19:43.626
Well, hey, how about this?

19:43.628 --> 19:46.129
Whether we're friends,
not friends,

19:46.131 --> 19:47.797
scattered around the world,
no matter what,

19:47.799 --> 19:49.932
let's all promise to meet
in front of this building

19:49.934 --> 19:52.235
exactly 20 years
from tonight at 8:00 p.m.

19:52.237 --> 19:53.903
and have dinner
like we always do.

19:53.905 --> 19:55.171
Aw! I love it.

19:55.173 --> 19:56.205
Okay?

19:56.207 --> 19:57.273
Putting it
in my phone right now.

19:57.275 --> 19:58.474
Yeah, me, too.

19:59.777 --> 20:02.078
My phone doesn't
have a calendar.

20:06.383 --> 20:08.618
It's all right, I'll just
write it on my hand.

20:10.854 --> 20:12.955
And it's done.

20:12.957 --> 20:14.290
Yup, we're all in.

20:14.292 --> 20:16.225
All right, I'll see you guys
in 20 years.

